			<trans-unit id="settings.intro" resname="settings.intro">
				<source>These settings apply to the TYPO3 backend login page. Use public resource paths such as EXT:your_extension/Resources/Public/... (same format as the core backend extension configuration). For the login background you can use a single local file, a random JPG/JPEG/PNG/WebP from a FAL folder (direct children of the selected folder), or a remote random image (third-party services; each page load may request a new image). Login logo, logo alt, and footnote show values from the core backend extension settings when this extension has not stored its own value yet.</source>
			</trans-unit>
			<trans-unit id="settings.loginBackgroundFalFolder" resname="settings.loginBackgroundFalFolder">
				<source>Background image folder</source>
			</trans-unit>
			<trans-unit id="settings.loginBackgroundFalFolder.browse" resname="settings.loginBackgroundFalFolder.browse">
				<source>Browse…</source>
			</trans-unit>
			<trans-unit id="settings.loginBackgroundFalFolder.hint" resname="settings.loginBackgroundFalFolder.hint">
				<source>Select a folder from your file mounts. Each login page load uses one random image with extension JPG, JPEG, PNG, or WebP from the folder’s direct contents (not subfolders). If none are found, the bundled road.webp fallback is used. You can also paste a combined identifier (e.g. 1:/path).</source>
			</trans-unit>
			<trans-unit id="settings.loginBackgroundImage" resname="settings.loginBackgroundImage">
